            <h3>St. Angela’s vocational secondary school for the deaf</h3>
            <p>Students with hearing problems can get specialized education at
              St. Angela's Vocational Secondary School
              for the Deaf. The school offers a wide range of courses, including
              vocational training, to provide
              students real-world skills that improve their employability and
              independence. In order to guarantee an
              accessible learning environment, St. Angela's uses sign language
              and other helpful communication
              techniques.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <img src="/images/Kenya.jpg"
              alt="Kenya Community Centre for Learning">
            <h3>Kenya Community Centre for Learning</h3>
            <p>Kenya Community Centre for Learning (KCCL) offers a comprehensive
              range of services designed to support
              students with diverse learning challenges. These services include
              assessment and placements to identify
              learning needs and create Individualized Education Plans (IEPs).
              Additionally, KCCL provides various
              therapy services such as occupational, physiotherapy, art, music,
              dance, and counseling therapies. The
              center also offers academic and vocational programs tailored to
              students with mild to severe learning
              difficulties, aiming to foster holistic educational and personal
              development.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <img src="/images/joytown1.jpg"
              alt="Joytown Primary School for physically impaired">
            <h3>Joytown Primary School for physically impaired</h3>
            <p>A specialized school in Thika, Kenya, Joytown Primary School for
              the Physically Impaired is committed to
              giving kids with physical disabilities high-quality instruction
              and assistance. With amenities created
              to meet the individual requirements of each student, such as
              wheelchair ramps, modified classrooms, and
              specific teaching materials, the school provides a secure and
              easily accessible setting. </p>
          </div>
        </div>
